### Known Issues
- ~~**Drawdown calculation bug**~~ FIXED 2026-06-12: stake is capped at
  available bankroll, backtests halt at bankruptcy (`busted` flag), and
  drawdown percent is bounded in [-100%, 0]
  (`src/trading.py::compute_drawdown_metrics`).
- ~~**Real/simulated metrics filename mismatch**~~ FIXED 2026-06-12: canonical
  artifact is `backtest/real_kalshi_metrics.json`; the promotion framework
  reads both legacy schemas and fails the new `trading_source_real` gate when
  only simulated evidence exists.
- **Settlement rounding semantics** VERIFIED 2026-06-12 against every settled
  contract row (n=14,116, 100% agreement): Kalshi settles on the rounded
  integer °F with `lo <= round(TMAX) < hi` bucket semantics. All bucket
  probability/outcome code now routes through `src/bucket_semantics.py`.
- **Synthesis MLP is weak**: the pipeline's synthesis stage is a 6-feature
  recalibration of the base model's own (mu, sigma) — it uses NO NWP/MOS
  forecast data (the richer `src/synthesis_model.py` station+NWP fusion is
  not wired into the pipeline). This is the single most likely reason cities
  fail the `beats_nws` gate. A Gaussian-NLL convergence pathology (sigma
  absorbing the initial mu residual) was also fixed 2026-06-12; the Phase-2
  model work should replace this stage with MOS-residual models.
- **ASOS training gap** — only the NYC reference model was trained on ASOS
  (IEM) hourly data. All expansion cities currently train on GHCN daily data,
  creating a training/inference mismatch since live inference uses
  ASOS-derived features. ASOS also publishes hourly — it is the only
  temperature source available by the 7am ET market-day cutoff, which GHCN
  (multi-day lag) can never satisfy (see Section 6, Phase E).

