## 2) Contract Alignment & System Constraints

### Contract alignment expectations
Before model changes or live deployment for any city, enforce:
- Observation site and settlement definition match the contract target exactly.
- Bucket boundaries and inclusivity/exclusivity match exchange rules exactly.
- Daily boundary (local day vs UTC) is explicitly encoded in preprocessing.

### Non-negotiable operational constraint
- Live decisions must use only inputs available by an early-morning cutoff.
- Delayed training-grade datasets are allowed offline, but not as live-time features.

### Promotion preconditions (repo policy)
- No time leakage
- Calibrated probabilities only
- Positive EV after realistic costs
- Risk controls and kill-switch checks validated

